cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL 

The paper deals with the security and decentralization aspects of the Ethereum network, which are typically studied in the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also involves analyzing the computational costs of transactions, which falls under the cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-categories.
